title: IEEE 802.11ac-2013
summary: IEEE 802.11ac-2013 or 802.11ac is a wireless networking standard in the 802.11 set of protocols (which is part of the Wi-Fi networking family), providing high-throughput wireless local area networks (WLANs) on the 5Â GHz band.[lower-alpha 1] The standard has been retroactively labelled as Wi-Fi 5 by Wi-Fi Alliance.[1][2]
